candidate_text:
Here is a poem about deep sleep, every line starting with the letter G:

Gently darkness falls upon my eyes 
Gliding softly into dreamless skies 
Guiding me to where my soul can roam 
Gathering strength for another day at home 
Gifting me the rest I need so dear 
Giving in to slumber's soothing fear 
Gathering speed as I descend below 
Groping for the edge of consciousness to know 
Growing heavier, and harder still 
Gasping slow,{\i} descending down the hill 
Giving up all thoughts and worries free 
Grasped by somnolence's silky tentaclesassistant
